      passage: `Writer Lydia Davis observed that while traditional literary forms, such as the novel, are recognizable as such even as they evolve, there are more ______ forms that might, for example, borrow elements from both fables and realist narratives to make something unconventional. Davis&rsquo;s own very short literary pieces arguably fit in this category, since they straddle the line between prose and poetry.`,
